On Monday, Bank of England governor Andrew Bailey told MPs that the war in Ukraine will cause "apocalyptic" food shortages that the bank is "helpless" to protect Britons from. Reacting to these comments, Piers Morgan tweeted: "Doesn’t strike me as very helpful for the Governor of the Bank of England to use words like ‘apocalyptic’ unless we’re actually in an Apocalypse - in which case it doesn’t matter what he says because we’ll all be dead." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 